<subSubSection id="2991F1B8475106B77456F09981FDCA17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3598AC8EA3818C361CB331CA26840C4B" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis. Distinguished from all other genera of Botiinae by the unique presence of a sickle-shaped anterior process of the premaxilla, surrounding a cavity between left and right processes; rostral process short, without ridge along inner edge.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="359D37289C21C0CDB97A576D56B5E66B" pageNumber="13">Distinguished from other lineages within the subfamily Botiinae by the following combination of characters: Mental lobe not developed in a barbel, with a pair of fleshy papillae at its anterior edge. Fronto-parietal fontanelle large, wide. Anterior chamber of gas bladder partly covered by bony capsule; posterior chamber large. Top of supraethmoid narrow. Optic foramen large. Suborbital spine not strongly curved backwards, bifid. Head naked (based on Taki, 1972: 74, 76). Colour pattern: regular, narrow bars throughout life, in some species with overimposed longitudinal rows of black spots.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AECB01DFCD36E7F530B24D70629D8B7D" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FED54DDF6B27C946C9D7468DFF6C715F" pageNumber="13">
Remarks. The valid name for the lineage called 
<taxonomicName id="8A821AF06B8DCCDF13FCA8E5CEFF3838" authority="Mcclelland, 1839" authorityName="Mcclelland" authorityYear="1839" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Hymenophysa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hymenophysa</taxonomicName>
by Fang (1936), Nalbant(1963, 2002), Taki (1972) and others is 
<taxonomicName id="FBB14D39CFB04C17E3D9AF34198D8AAD" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CA0CF450-BB57-4696-9505-8CBD7D102374" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Syncrossus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Syncrossus Blyth 1860:166" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Syncrossus Blyth, 1860</taxonomicName>
. Blyth (1860: 166) originally included two species in his 
<taxonomicName id="2FAD140DC1A5AF762ABAE7768A75AFD1" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CA0CF450-BB57-4696-9505-8CBD7D102374" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Syncrossus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Syncrossus Blyth 1860:166" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Syncrossus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B6F2DABC750F32E9A752F81F0132C7E4" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E73729B7-A111-4ACE-9ABA-94ADF6BEADB7" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Syncrossus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Syncrossus berdmorei Blyth 1860:166" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="berdmorei">S. berdmorei Blyth, 1860</taxonomicName>
and &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="07524C65FC84693FB17054CBC777ECD2" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Schistura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="grandis">Schistura grandis</taxonomicName>
apud McClelland&quot;. The last name is a deliberate application of a previous misidentification[ICZN art. 67.2.1], and therefore two species are included. The type species, by subsequent designation by Jordan (1919b: 294) is 
<taxonomicName id="C17E33CF849BD7EDA19DCB7DBD64AF74" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E73729B7-A111-4ACE-9ABA-94ADF6BEADB7" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Syncrossus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Syncrossus berdmorei Blyth 1860:166" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="berdmorei">S. berdmorei</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AAF34042A596440C959913594CEDAA97" pageNumber="13">
The species called 
<taxonomicName id="3D49F869BCB689AB92BFC5E5355B24C5" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:397690FF-D0FB-42E4-8450-1A48C1606DDB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia Hymenophysa kwangsiensis Fang 1936:13" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hymenophysa">B. hymenophysa</taxonomicName>
by Taki (1972) is 
<taxonomicName id="EBEA64357E301652474C6BD17FF2F9D7" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:66172B23-2725-4A8B-9C41-1FBF23CE70AA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Botia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Botia helodes Sauvage 1876:99 [3]" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="helodes">B. helodes</taxonomicName>
(see Kottelat, 1984; Nalbant &amp; Bianco, 1984).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
